---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<style>
  .node-bg { fill: #EAE0D5; transition: fill 0.3s ease; }
  .node-stroke { stroke: #A3B899; transition: stroke 0.3s ease; }
  .center-bg { fill: #D6CBBF; transition: fill 0.3s ease; }
  
  :global(.dark) .node-bg { fill: #2B2F2A; }
  :global(.dark) .node-stroke { stroke: #3F372C; }
  :global(.dark) .center-bg { fill: #3F372C; }
  
  :global(.dark) .node-text { fill: #E2E2E2 !important; }

  .svg-line {
    stroke: #A3B899;
    transition: stroke 0.3s ease;
  }
  :global(.dark) .svg-line {
    stroke: #4A5D3F;
  }
  
  .svg-marker path {
    fill: #A3B899;
    transition: fill 0.3s ease;
  }
  :global(.dark) .svg-marker path {
    fill: #4A5D3F;
  }
</style>

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="The personal journey of Daniel Kim, tracing the trajectory from computer vision to Bayesian reinforcement learning."
>
  <h1>The Personal Journey</h1>
  <p style="font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); max-width: 38rem;">
    Tracing the academic trajectory from the foundational mechanics of computer vision to the profound statistical rigour of Bayesian reinforcement learning.
  </p>



  <div class="svg-container" style="margin: 4rem 0; display: flex; justify-content: center; overflow: visible;">
    <!-- SVG Content Unchanged -->
    <svg width="400" height="400" viewBox="0 0 400 400" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
      <defs>
        <marker id="arrow" class="svg-marker" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" orient="auto-start-reverse">
          <path d="M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z" />
        </marker>
      </defs>

      <line x1="184" y1="88" x2="95" y2="242" class="svg-line" stroke-width="1.5" marker-start="url(#arrow)" marker-end="url(#arrow)" />
      <line x1="111" y1="270" x2="289" y2="270" class="svg-line" stroke-width="1.5" marker-start="url(#arrow)" marker-end="url(#arrow)" />
      <line x1="305" y1="242" x2="216" y2="88" class="svg-line" stroke-width="1.5" marker-start="url(#arrow)" marker-end="url(#arrow)" />

      <line x1="200" y1="92" x2="200" y2="172" class="svg-line" stroke-width="2" marker-start="url(#arrow)" marker-end="url(#arrow)" />
      <line x1="107" y1="254" x2="176" y2="214" class="svg-line" stroke-width="2" marker-start="url(#arrow)" marker-end="url(#arrow)" />
      <line x1="293" y1="254" x2="224" y2="214" class="svg-line" stroke-width="2" marker-start="url(#arrow)" marker-end="url(#arrow)" />

      <g>
        <circle cx="200" cy="200" r="28" class="center-bg" stroke="var(--color-text-primary)" stroke-width="2" />
        <text x="200" y="196" class="node-text" font-family="var(--font-sans)" font-size="12" font-weight="600" fill="var(--color-text-primary)" text-anchor="middle">Daniel</text>
        <text x="200" y="210" class="node-text" font-family="var(--font-sans)" font-size="12" font-weight="600" fill="var(--color-text-primary)" text-anchor="middle">Kim</text>
      </g>

      <g style="cursor: help;">
        <title>Rigorous Statistical Inference</title>
        <circle cx="200" cy="60" r="32" class="node-bg node-stroke" stroke-width="2" />
        <text x="200" y="56" class="node-text" font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="10" font-weight="600" fill="var(--color-text-primary)" text-anchor="middle">Stats</text>
        <text x="200" y="70" class="node-text" font-family="var(--font-serif)" font-size="10" font-style="italic" fill="var(--color-text-secondary)" text-anchor="middle">(Theory)</text>
      </g>

      <g style="cursor: help;">
        <title>High-performance Systems</title>
        <circle cx="79" cy="270" r="32" class="node-bg node-stroke" stroke-width="2" />
        <text x="79" y="266" class="node-text" font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="10" font-weight="600" fill="var(--color-text-primary)" text-anchor="middle">CS</text>
        <text x="79" y="280" class="node-text" font-family="var(--font-serif)" font-size="10" font-style="italic" fill="var(--color-text-secondary)" text-anchor="middle">(System)</text>
      </g>

      <g style="cursor: help;">
        <title>Optimal Sequential Decisions</title>
        <circle cx="321" cy="270" r="32" class="node-bg node-stroke" stroke-width="2" />
        <text x="321" y="266" class="node-text" font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="10" font-weight="600" fill="var(--color-text-primary)" text-anchor="middle">RL</text>
        <text x="321" y="280" class="node-text" font-family="var(--font-serif)" font-size="10" font-style="italic" fill="var(--color-text-secondary)" text-anchor="middle">(Domain)</text>
      </g>
    </svg>
  </div>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
    <h2>Current Focus</h2>
    <p>
      My primary research trajectory centres on Bayesian Reinforcement Learning, with a specific emphasis on sample efficiency in high-dimensional state spaces and sequential decision-making under epistemic uncertainty.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
    <h2>Academic Background</h2>
    <p>
      I possess dual-disciplinary foundations in Computer Science and Applied Statistics from Yonsei University, bridging empirical scalability with theoretical guarantees. This confluence of disciplines informs my approach to architecting mathematically robust intelligent systems.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
    <h2>Methodological Strengths</h2>
    <p>
      My research philosophy is underpinned by four core pillars: probabilistic reasoning, decisions under uncertainty, structural statistical modelling, and principled, rigorous experimentation.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
    <h2>What Kinds of Problems Excite Me</h2>
    <p>
      I am profoundly motivated by the challenge of bridging the representational capacity of deep neural networks with the inferential rigour of mathematical statistics, cultivating methodologies that are both highly performant and statistically sound.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
    <h2>Foundational Explorations</h2>
    <p>
      Through early practical engagements with real-time object detection pipelines (such as YOLOX and DeepSORT), I witnessed first-hand the inherent vulnerabilities of deterministic models within high-dimensional decision systems. This pivotal observation precipitated my academic pivot towards Statistical Reinforcement Learning, where the explicit quantification and bounding of uncertainty form the crux of the methodology.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
    <h2>Scientific Visualisation &amp; Graphical Inference</h2>
    <p>
      I strongly believe that research must be accessible to be impactful. I leverage scientific visualisation techniques to distil high-dimensional stochastic processes into intuitive, publication-grade graphical abstracts, ensuring structural algorithmic clarity resonates across diverse academic audiences.
    </p>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
